lead_paragraph: Paris St Germain claimed a bittersweet 4-0 victory against Stade Rennais on Sunday, edging closer to Nice after the leaders suffered their first Ligue 1 defeat but losing talismanic striker Edinson Cavani through injury.

headline.print_headline: PSG Win but Lose Cavani as Leaders Nice Slump to First Defeat
headline.main: PSG Win but Lose Cavani as Leaders Nice Slump to First Defeat
